The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 7 injured by buses in hurry 

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Seven persons, including two women, were injured on Friday morning in two accidents caused by rash driving. Of the injured, two were admitted to hospital. Their condition is stated to be critical.

 According to police, the first mishap occurred around 10 pm at the intersection of Jawaharlal Nehru Road and Outram Road. 

 ?After leaving the Babughat terminus, a private bus on route 212 was speeding along Outram Road, when the driver lost control and the vehicle hit two taxis at the crossing. Thereafter, the bus collided with a minibus,? said Anuj Sharma, deputy commissioner of police (headquarters).

 Policemen and passers-by rushed six persons to SSKM Hospital. Four of the injured were in the taxi, while two others were minibus passengers. One of them was admitted to hospital as he had received head injuries.

 The driver of the minibus was arrested, deputy commissioner Sharma said.

 The second accident occurred around 11.30 pm on Shyamaprasad Mukherjee Road, in front of Bhowanipore police station. A minibus first rammed into the roadside railing and then mounted the pavement. It knocked down a 22-year-old youth, identified as Shyamal Jana, who was standing on the pavement.

 Jana was rushed to SSKM Hospital where his condition was said to be serious. The driver of the minibus fled.




